descriptions.description: Plot: Indicates plot number. Block: Indicates block number. #: Indicates strip number, 1-45. S#: Indicates compartment number within strip, 1-15. Removal: 1=Late Fall, 2=Early Spring, 3=Spring. Prop_crop: % crop alleles in each cross type. Cross: cross type identifying name. Mat: Maternal parent of cross type. Pat: Paternal parent of cross type. Q_able: counted dead, R3 only. #peek: open achenes, not yet technically germinated. #_germ: # germinated seeds. #germB: # germinated seeds, but with slight browning, indicating earlier germination date. Total_germ: #_germ + #germB. #_in_GC: # of seeds removed from strip and placed in growth chamber (GC). GC_g’d1: germinated seeds at first census. GC_g’d2: germinated seeds at second census. TZ: # seed put into tetrazolium chloride for viability testing. TZ_d: # seed found to be dormant by TZ test. TZ_DEAD: # seed found to be dead by TZ test. #dormant: figure used for “total ungerminated” in text. iDead: initial dead seed out of the burial strip. GC_Dead: seed determined to be dead in the growth chamber. Dead_Total: iDead + TZ Dead + GC_Dead. FG’d: Seeds determined to have germinated in the Fall, after the Late Fall date. Mt: empty achenes—never fertilized. Total: seeds – mt seeds.
